Kismet Prerequisites
System packages
--------------------------------------------
sudo apt update
sudo apt install kismet kismet-plugins build-essential libpcap-dev \
libusb-1.0-0-dev libdw-dev libnl-3-dev libnl-genl-3-dev

Alfa card drivers — the AWUS036ACH uses the rtl8812au driver which doesn't ship with most kernels by default:
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
sudo apt install dkms
git clone https://github.com/aircrack-ng/rtl8812au
cd rtl8812au
sudo make dkms_install
*After install, confirm the card is visible:*
iwconfig
# or
iw dev
*Add user to kismet group so students don't need to run as root:
sudo usermod -aG kismet $USER
*Log out and back in for it to take effect.

Monitor Mode
--------------------------------------------------------
Before launching Kismet, put the Alfa into monitor mode:
sudo airmon-ng check kill    # kills interfering processes
sudo airmon-ng start wlan0   # creates wlan0mon
Confirm with iwconfig wlan0mon — should show Mode: Monitor.

Basic Kismet Usage for DF
---------------------------------------------------------
Launch:
kismet -c wlan0mon

Kismet spins up a web UI at http://localhost:2501 — open it in a browser. Default login is set on first run.
What students are looking for:

SSID of the exercise AP
BSSID (MAC address)
Signal strength (dBm) — this is their compass
Channel

DF technique with the Yagi:
--------------------------------------------------------------
The Yagi gives directionality that the Alfa's stock antenna doesn't. Basic process:

Start with omnidirectional scan to identify the target SSID and note its signal level
Mount or hold the Yagi and rotate slowly — signal increases as you point toward the source
Take a bearing from at least two separated positions — triangulate to narrow the hide location
Move toward the stronger bearing, take another reading, repeat

Signal strength tip for the AAR: Kismet displays RSSI in dBm — closer to 0 is stronger (-40 dBm is strong, -80 dBm is weak). 
Students sometimes get this backwards initially. Worth a quick brief before the evolution.

Quick Kismet Config Tip
-------------------------------------------------------------------
Drop a kismet.conf override in /etc/kismet/kismet_site.conf so students don't have to configure anything on launch:
source=wlan0mon
log_prefix=/home/student/captures/
log_types=kismetdb,pcapng

The pcapng log is what they'll use for the AAR packet review.



